            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1691681113066-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1691681113066-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on) into fries</p><p>Add the <strong>fries</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1691681119826-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1691681119826-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1691681119826-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1691681119826-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1691681119826-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the<strong> grated onion </strong>and<strong> half</strong> the <strong>grated garlic</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) in a large bowl with the <strong>dried oregano</strong>, <strong>pork & beef mince </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up until thoroughly combined (clean hands are the best way!)</p><p>Divide into 8 <span class=\"text-danger\">[16]</span> and shape them into meatballs</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1691681124191-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1691681124191-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1691681124191-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1691681124191-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1691681124191-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>meatballs</strong> and <strong>diced onion</strong> to the pan and cook for 2 min on each side or until browned and the onion has softened</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1691681127393-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1691681127393-x400.jpg",
